.TH CODEX_APP_SERVER_GENERATE_JSON_SCHEMA 1 "July 2026" "codex-cli 0.142.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codex\-app\-server\-generate\-json\-schema \- [experimental] Generate JSON Schema for the app server protocol
.SH SYNOPSIS
.EX
Usage: codex app\-server generate\-json\-schema [OPTIONS] \-\-out <DIR>

.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
[experimental] Generate JSON Schema for the app server protocol
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config <key=value>
Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`. Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.
.PP
Examples: \- `\-c model="o3"` \- `\-c 'sandbox_permissions=["disk\-full\-read\-access"]'` \- `\-c shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-out <DIR>
Output directory where the schema bundle will be written
.TP
.B \-\-enable <FEATURE>
Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=true`
.TP
.B \-\-experimental
Include experimental methods and fields in the generated output
.TP
.B \-\-disable <FEATURE>
Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=false`
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help (see a summary with '\-h')
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1),
.BR codex\-app\-server (1)
